<typeStatus id="54F6E6B0CE48EC627EEEFCDFC7D0CB66" box="[151,209,836,862]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Type</typeStatus>
species (by original designation): 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D2391CE48EC627C1CFCDFC4E7CB66" authority="Philippi, 1836" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1836" box="[613,998,836,862]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rupestris">
<emphasis id="B9398400CE48EC627C1CFCDFC434CB65" box="[613,821,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Bulimus rupestris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC25E3CE48EC627D45FCDFC4E7CB66" author="Philippi, R. A." box="[828,998,836,862]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref36698" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1836) Enumeratio molluscorum Siciliae cum viventium tum in tellure tertiaria fossilium, quae in itinere suo observavit. Schropp, Berolini (= Berlin), 14 &amp; 267 pp., 12 pls." type="book" year="1836">Philippi, 1836</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF25812CE48EC627EBFFCF1C531CCAB" blockId="39.[151,1436,800,1171]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
Notes.— 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D2391CE48EC627F55FCF1C6B3CBBB" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1894" box="[300,434,874,899]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9398400CE48EC627F55FCF1C6B3CBBB" box="[300,434,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Rupestrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still is the most poorly known genus in the family. The molecular data place this genus as the sister-group next to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D2391CE48EC627C5AFC0AC568CB92" authorityName="W. Turton" authorityYear="1831" box="[547,617,913,938]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Abida" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9398400CE48EC627C5AFC0AC568CB92" box="[547,617,913,938]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Abida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC25E3CE48EC627CD3FC0AC4A3CB93" author="Kokshoorn, B." box="[682,930,913,939]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref35737" refString="Kokshoorn, B. (2008) Resolving Riddles and Presenting New Puzzles in Chondrinidae Phylogenetics. PhD thesis, Leiden University, 192 pp." type="book" year="2008">Kokshoorn 2008: 34</bibRefCitation>
). Additional morphological and molecular work is necessary but the material to enable such studies is not (yet) available, in particular not for the African taxa. Pilsbry (1918: 332–356) provisionally accepted 16 species, 5 of which are endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="498996F0CE48EC627A99FC45C225CBC0" box="[1248,1316,990,1016]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Sicily</collectingRegion>
and 8 are endemic to northern Africa. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC25E3CE48EC627F9FFB9EC5B8CC27" author="Beckmann, K. - H." box="[486,697,1029,1055]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="49 - 78" refId="ref33589" refString="Beckmann, K. - H. (2002) Elemente einer Revision der endemischen Rupestrellen Siziliens. In: Falkner, M., Groh, K. &amp; Speight, M. C. D. (Eds), Collectanea Malacologica, 49 - 78, Hackenheim." type="book chapter" year="2002">Beckmann (2002)</bibRefCitation>
recognized 4 species as endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="498996F0CE48EC627A1EFB9EC3ADCC27" box="[1127,1196,1029,1055]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Sicily</collectingRegion>
, with 11 subspecific taxa in total.To stabilize the nomenclature of the two most widespread species, viz. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D2391CE48EC627A13FBB7C3ECCC7D" baseAuthorityName="Cantraine" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1130,1261,1068,1093]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="philippii">
<emphasis id="B9398400CE48EC627A13FBB7C3ECCC7D" box="[1130,1261,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">R. philippii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D2391CE48EC627B5FFBB7C295CC7D" baseAuthorityName="Roth" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1318,1428,1068,1093]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rhodia">
<emphasis id="B9398400CE48EC627B5FFBB7C295CC7D" box="[1318,1428,1068,1093]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">R. rhodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a 
<typeStatus id="54F6E6B0CE48EC627ED2FBC9C617CC54" box="[171,278,1106,1132]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">lectotype</typeStatus>
is here selected for the former species. Additionally we present an uncritical, annotated list of currently recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D2391CE48EC627F13FBE2C6F1CCAA" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1894" box="[362,496,1145,1170]" class="Gastropoda" family="Chondrinidae" genus="Rupestrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9398400CE48EC627F13FBE2C6F1CCAA" box="[362,496,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Rupestrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa.
</paragraph>
